		<label>HK PSG1 (Irons 50Rnd)</label>
		<description>Caliber: 7.62x51mm NATO. 50-round detachable mag. Semi-Automatic.
		
The Heckler &amp; Koch PSG1 (Präzisionsschützengewehr 1, or "precision marksman rifle 1") is a German designated marksman rifle first produced in 1972. It is built off of H&amp;K's G3 rifle, though it has been substantially modified with a strengthened receiver, a specialized sniping stock, an adjustable trigger, and a heavy free-floating match barrel providing an accuracy of better than 1 MOA. Factory PSG1 rifles are shipped with an attached Hensoldt ZF 6x42 scope, although this one has had its scope and mount removed.

This one has been fitted with a 50-round drum magazine originally designed for H&amp;K's G8 machine gun.</description>
